<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,358,1967]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,358,383]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Description.</emphasis>
Small, fragile empoascines marked with red and brown pigment. Head including eyes slightly narrower than maximum width of pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[674,779,394,419]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Figs 
<number box="[733,779,395,419]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="1.3">1, 3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Vertex in dorsal view shorter than width between eyes, anterior margin slightly produced medially (
<figureCitation box="[645,746,430,455]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Figs 
<number box="[702,746,431,455]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
</figureCitation>
), profile of transition to face rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1181,1250,430,455]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Fig. 
<number box="[1233,1250,431,455]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Coronal suture distinct, not reaching anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[589,693,466,491]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Figs 
<number box="[647,693,467,491]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="1.3">1, 3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Face broad, convex in profile, lateral frontal suture extended to ocelli but not continuing to midline (
<figureCitation box="[568,638,502,527]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Fig. 
<number box="[621,638,503,527]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ocelli on margin about equidistant between eye and midline (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Figs 
<number pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="3.4">3, 4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum large, more than twice as long as crown (
<figureCitation box="[775,878,538,563]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Figs 
<number box="[833,878,539,563]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="1.3">1, 3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Forewing narrow, rounded apically, apical cells occupying almost one-third of the total length, veins 
<collectingCountry box="[762,796,575,598]" name="Poland" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">RP</collectingCountry>
and MP’ confluent pre-apically for short distance, both arise from r cell and MP”+CuA’ from m cell; third apical cell broadened at base, slightly narrowed apically (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,167,647,671]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hindwing with CuA branched, point of branching distad of coalescence of CuA with MP” (
<figureCitation box="[1265,1352,646,671]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Fig. 
<number box="[1321,1352,647,671]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Front femur with dorsoapical pair of macrosetae, AM 
<number box="[698,707,683,707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="1.0">1</number>
enlarged and situated on ventral margin, intercalary row with 
<number box="[1422,1436,683,707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="1.0">1</number>
large basal seta and 
<number box="[386,400,718,743]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="6.0">6</number>
smaller setae more distad. 
<collectingCountry box="[718,774,718,743]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur macrosetae 
<number box="[995,1012,719,743]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1031,1041,719,743]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="1.0">1</number>
, row AV with 
<number box="[1215,1243,719,743]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="13.0">13</number>
macrosetae near apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,358,1967]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Male basal abdominal sternal apodemes well developed, parallel sided or slightly tapered (
<figureCitation box="[1248,1355,790,815]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Figs 
<number box="[1308,1355,791,815]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="7.8">7, 8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Male pygofer elongate, with several rigid microsetae along posterior margin, ventral appendage absent (
<figureCitation box="[1264,1337,826,851]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Figs 
<number box="[1322,1337,826,851]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="9.055" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="5.11">5</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1351,1423,827,851]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1546,1569]" captionTargetBox="[268,1312,193,1478]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,142,1525]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 11. male genitalia, left lateral view; 12. pygofer side, left lateral view; 13. pygofer side, dorsal view; 14. anal tube appendage, left lateral view; 15. aedeagus, left lateral view; 16. same, dorsal view; 17. valve, subgenital plate, and paramere, ventral view; 18. paramere; 19. valve and subgenital plate, left lateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm (Figs 11 – 14, 17, 19); 0.05 mm (Figs 15, 16, 18)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259786/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">11–13</figureCitation>
), dorsal bridge long (
<figureCitation box="[369,442,862,887]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Figs 
<number box="[426,442,862,887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="6.12">6</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[453,484,863,887]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1546,1569]" captionTargetBox="[268,1312,193,1478]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,142,1525]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 11. male genitalia, left lateral view; 12. pygofer side, left lateral view; 13. pygofer side, dorsal view; 14. anal tube appendage, left lateral view; 15. aedeagus, left lateral view; 16. same, dorsal view; 17. valve, subgenital plate, and paramere, ventral view; 18. paramere; 19. valve and subgenital plate, left lateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm (Figs 11 – 14, 17, 19); 0.05 mm (Figs 15, 16, 18)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259786/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">12</figureCitation>
). Sternite IX well developed (
<figureCitation box="[819,892,862,887]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Figs 
<number box="[876,892,862,887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="5.11">5</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[904,976,863,887]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1546,1569]" captionTargetBox="[268,1312,193,1478]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[226,1360,142,1525]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 11. male genitalia, left lateral view; 12. pygofer side, left lateral view; 13. pygofer side, dorsal view; 14. anal tube appendage, left lateral view; 15. aedeagus, left lateral view; 16. same, dorsal view; 17. valve, subgenital plate, and paramere, ventral view; 18. paramere; 19. valve and subgenital plate, left lateral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm (Figs 11 – 14, 17, 19); 0.05 mm (Figs 15, 16, 18)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259786/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
11, 
<number box="[945,976,863,887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate robust, relatively short and broad, base articulated to sternite IX, without basolateral extension, apex extended slightly beyond pygofer side, A-group setae absent, D-group setae undifferentiated, B-group setae scattered in two to three rows in apical half, C-group reduced to single preapical macroseta (
<figureCitation box="[747,848,970,995]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[271,1325,643,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[251,1335,626,1863]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Rubiparvus bistigma Xu, Dietrich &amp; Qin, sp. nov. 1. male adult, dorsal view; 2. same, left lateral view; 3. head and thorax, dorsal view; 4. face; 5. male genitalia, left lateral view; 6. same, dorsal view; 7. abdominal apodemes; 8. same, variant; 9. forewing; 10. hind wing. Scale bars = 0.2 mm (Figs 1 – 8); 1 mm (Figs 9, 10)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259785/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Figs 
<number box="[804,848,970,995]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" value="5.6">5, 6</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
